    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Backpropagation is the chain rule applied to a computation graph. Capucci (2021) shows this is a lens: the forward pass computes the function, the backward pass transports gradients. The universal approximation theorem says one hidden layer suffices for any continuous function -- but it says nothing about how many neurons you need or how easy it is to train.</p>

